  "opening_lines": [
    {
      "line": 1,
      "text": "‘Published"
    },
    {
      "line": 7,
      "text": "Whether admired from a Uistante of 22,000 miles or 20 feet ours is an ocean planet,"
    },
    {
      "line": 10,
      "text": "i - dazzling blue, dominated in every respect by its water."
    },
    {
      "line": 13,
      "text": "a A. couple years ago we had a Watershed Issue of CoEvolution, deservedly popular, which"
    },
    {
      "line": 14,
      "text": "a er forward a politics of watershed-consciousness, utterly local - where and how the"
    },
    {
      "line": 15,
      "text": "life-blood flows in your locale. Now drift down that flow to the sea. Though still AROLCLE"
    },
    {
      "line": 18,
      "text": "a : Ocean-consciousness is inescapably planetary. Just so the salty first : 03 pages of this"
    },
    {
      "line": 21,
      "text": "Oceans Issue. (The last 40 pages are CQ business as usual.)"
    },
    {
      "line": 23,
      "text": "The guest-editors of the section are experienced on three valuable counts - Biitay edit,"
    },
    {
      "line": 24,
      "text": "they know nautical material as few alive, and they mess with boats. Working out of"
    },
    {
      "line": 25,
      "text": "Penobscot Bay in Maine, George Putz and Peter Spectre have co-edited 6% volumes of"
    },
    {
      "line": 26,
      "text": "_. The Mariner’s Catalog, a wondrous access-and-assessment publication. (A seventh volume"
    },
    {
      "line": 27,
      "text": "is due late this fall.) Over the years they have accumulated material and ideas too oceanic"
    },
    {
      "line": 28,
      "text": "for their boat-oriented catalogs but just right for CoEvolution. Hence ahappy collaboration"
    },
    {
      "line": 29,
      "text": "this summer in Sausalito - different coast, different ocean, same water, same truth."
    },
    {
      "line": 31,
      "text": "I keep coming back to a remark by David Crosby, the public musician and private"
    },
    {
      "line": 32,
      "text": "mariner, that turned up in Rolling Stone a few years ago. For me it sums up what the sea"
    },
    {
      "line": 33,
      "text": "does for the individual and what it may yet do for humankind. Crosby said:"
    },
    {
      "line": 36,
      "text": "“You can’t bullshit the ocean. It’s not listening, you know what I mean?”"
    },
    {
      "line": 39,
      "text": "-Stewart Brand"
    },
    {
      "line": 40,
      "text": "Editor, The CoEvolution Quarterly"
